---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { getAllExperiments } from '../lib/experiments';

const experiments = getAllExperiments();
const latest = experiments.slice(0, 3);
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Codex Frontend Skill Research"
  description="A visual research project on improving Codex frontend design quality via iterative skill tuning."
>
  <section class="hero container">
    <p class="eyebrow">Why I Built This</p>
    <h1>I saw a benchmark, questioned fairness, and rebuilt the frontend skill for Codex.</h1>
    <p class="lede">
      After watching Theo compare models on frontend output quality, I noticed GPT was being tested with a
      Claude-oriented skill pack. This project tests a simple question: if we tune instructions specifically for Codex,
      how far can frontend quality move?
    </p>
    <div class="hero-actions">
      <a href="/experiments" class="btn btn-primary">See Experiment Results</a>
      <a href="/skills" class="btn btn-ghost">How Skill Changed</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="container section-grid">
    <article class="card">
      <h2>The Trigger</h2>
      <p>
        One shared instruction set does not transfer equally across model families. I wanted to test portability instead
        of assuming it.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>The Hypothesis</h2>
      <p>
        Codex is instruction-sensitive. With tighter constraints and better quality gates, outputs should move closer to
        Opus-like visual quality.
      </p>
    </article>
    <article class="card">
      <h2>What This Is Not</h2>
      <p>
        This is not model fine-tuning. It is instruction tuning only: fixed prompt, deliberate skill edits, and
        measurable route-by-route evaluation.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="container timeline">
    <h2>How It Runs</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>Keep `prompt.md` fixed.</li>
      <li>Change one skill axis per version.</li>
      <li>Generate fresh `/1.. /5` outputs.</li>
      <li>Score and critique against reference targets.</li>
      <li>Keep or drop the mutation for next version.</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="container">
    <div class="section-head-inline">
      <h2>Latest Iterations</h2>
      <a href="/experiments" class="inline-link">See all versions</a>
    </div>
    <div class="mini-grid">
      {
        latest.map((experiment) => (
          <article class="mini-card">
            <p class="eyebrow">{experiment.version}</p>
            <h3>{experiment.title}</h3>
            <p>{experiment.hypothesis}</p>
            <p class="muted small">
              {experiment.scoreOutOf20 !== null ? `${experiment.scoreOutOf20.toFixed(1)} / 20` : 'Score unavailable'}
            </p>
            <a class="inline-link" href={`/experiments/${experiment.version}`}>
              Open result set
            </a>
          </article>
        ))
      }
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
